The paper deals with the problem of undersampled phase retrieval, which is a common problem in signal processing and imaging. The proposed algorithms exploit sparsity in the signal, which is a key concept in many areas of computer science, including image processing (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the use of majorization-minimization, which is a popular optimization technique in many areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NA, and cs.SI.
